@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "How to Play";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
        <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/site.css" />
        <style>
            body {
                font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
                background-color: #f8f9fa;
                color: #343a40;
            }

            .container {
                max-width: 800px;
                margin: 0 auto;
                padding: 20px;
            }

            .header {
                margin-bottom: 40px;
                text-align: center;
            }

                .header h1 {
                    font-size: 2.5rem;
                    color: #007bff;
                }

            .content {
                font-size: 1.2rem;
            }

                .content h2 {
                    font-size: 1.5rem;
                    margin-top: 20px;
                    color: #0056b3;
                }

                .content ul {
                    margin-left: 20px;
                }

                    .content ul li {
                        margin-bottom: 10px;
                    }

            .footer {
                margin-top: 50px;
                text-align: center;
                font-size: 0.9rem;
                color: #6c757d;
            }
        </style>
     </head>
    <body>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="header">
                <h1>How to Play Minesweeper</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="content">
                <h2>Objective</h2>
                <p>The objective of Minesweeper is to clear a rectangular board containing hidden mines without detonating any of them, with the help of clues about the number of neighboring mines in each field.</p>
                
                <h2>Gameplay</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Click on a cell to reveal it. If it's a mine, you lose the game.</li>
                    <li>If the cell is not a mine, a number appears indicating how many mines are adjacent to (around) that cell. </li>
                    <li>Use the numbers to locate the mines and mark them with a flag</li>
                    <li>Right-click on a cell to place or remove a flag, indicating a suspected mine location.</li>
                    <li>Clear all the non-mine cells to win the game.</li>
                </ul>


                <h2>Tips and Strategies</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Start clicking cells in a corner or edge to reduce the chances of hitting a mine on your first click.</li>
                        <li>If you uncover a "1", look for safe cells adjacent to it. If there's only one hidden cell next to it, it must be a mine.</li>
                        <li>Use patterns and logical deduction to figure out where mines are located.</li>
                    </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="footer">
                <p>&copy; 2024 Minesweeper: Breanna Gernon, Daniel Rajotte, Rodrigo Martinez. CST-350</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>